
---


@startuml

' Entities involved in the system

class Bus {
  -id: String
  -lineNumber: Integer
}

class Line {
  -id: String
  -name: String
  -category: String
  -trajectories: List<Trajectory>
}

class Trajectory {
  -id: String
  -description: String
  -status: String (e.g., approved, pending, suspended, cancelled)
  -approvedDate: Date
  -cancellationDate: Date
  -submissionHistory: List<ApprovalRequest>
}

class ApprovalRequest {
  -requestDate: Date
  -townAuthorityFeedback: String
  -isApproved: Boolean
  -trajectory: Trajectory
}

class TownAuthority {
  -name: String
  -contact: String
}

class MENSO {
  -cardId: String
  -validFrom: Date
  -validUntil: Date
  -customer: Customer
  -trips: List<Trip>
}

class Trip {
  -tripId: String
  -date: Date
  -time: Time
  -line: Line
  -mensoCardUsed: Boolean
}

class Customer {
  -id: String
  -name: String
  -homeAddress: String
  -officeAddress: String
  -workingHours: String
  -mensoCards: List<MENSO>
  -invoices: List<Invoice>
}

class Invoice {
  -invoiceId: String
  -issueDate: Date
  -dueDate: Date
  -totalAmount: Float
  -discountApplied: Float
  -paidStatus: Boolean
  -customer: Customer
}

class MENSOSystem {
  -processTrip(): void
  -generateInvoice(): void
  -analyzeTravelPatterns(): void
}

' Associations

Bus --> Line : assigned to
Line --> Trajectory : includes
Trajectory --> ApprovalRequest : has submission history
Trajectory --> TownAuthority : requested by
MENSO --> Customer : belongs to
MENSO --> Trip : contains
Trip --> Line : taken on
Customer --> MENSO : owns
Customer --> Invoice : receives
Invoice --> Customer : issued to
MENSOSystem --> Trip : processes
MENSOSystem --> Invoice : generates
MENSOSystem --> Customer : analyzes

@enduml

---

### 🧩 Notes:
- The `Trajectory` can go through multiple approval requests (`ApprovalRequest`) until it is finally approved.
- A `Line` may include several `Trajectory` objects to support varying routes at different times.
- The `MENSO` system tracks all trips and uses that data for invoicing and analysis.
- Invoices are generated per customer, and they may receive multiple invoices before previous ones are paid.
- Personal information of customers is collected to analyze travel patterns.

